I‚Äôm loving TRUE! This is when I‚Äôve felt the strongest in my practice. I noticed I had to keep my eyes open during the flow today, when I normally like to keep them closed. I was off my balance and I think it‚Äôs because I lost so much healthy weight. My body is readjusting so many things, positioning of my limbs during movements where I had to alternate them, and now I don‚Äôt so much, and balance is another thing I‚Äôm getting readjusted to. I never fully mastered tree pose and now I‚Äôll have to relearn it, lol. When I gained a lot of weight I had to do these same adjustments, so it didn‚Äôt take me long to figure out that it‚Äôs probably the same in reverse. It‚Äôs taken me TIME to get here and yoga has been a big part of that. Yoga has helped me so much and I notice more and more how much more I treat my body as a human being instead of as a machine. Weird but true. I would not see myself as an organic being, but now I find every opportunity to baby myself. This is my version of taking my practice into the world with me for right now. As my practice grows, I‚Äôm sure I will in other ways too. Namaste üôèüèæ

AFTER a very hot day (36C) and spending time at the pool, I came to the mat late in the night where I was feeling refreshed and completely relaxed and so it was nice to take this yoga session and move at a pace that was fitting to me although I did challenge myself on more than one occasion.

It is great to know that there is repetition through out this True Journey and so I am always up to the next challenge, especially if on day, I am struggling through the motions.  I know that the same poses will be popping up again.  

As I am lacking flexibility I am still trying to work out where I belong on the mat when pigeon comes up but last night, I took in a good back stretch that was so needed.  I love coming to the mat and participating and giving my everything but sometimes I feel as though I am in too deep but to me, I have accepted that I am not flexible and it is just nice to find 30 minutes in the day where you are not having to think about what is going on around you, you just focus on yourself.  

The day had been focusing on myself and spending at least four hours in the water while the sun beat down and then spending 30 minutes on the mat as a way of bringing the day to a close was something that I really needed.  I am still struggling with tiredness, but I feel as though I am completely stress free and feeling rejuvinated after winding up day 9 of open.  

I haven't quite worked out where this yoga journey is taking me but I am getting the place of knowing just how good it feels to make it to the mat and stay there and be in the present with no care in the world.  I actually breathe a deep breath before stepping on the mat as a way of saying "I have arrived." and then I am just following and focusing on what I can learn in a time span of 30 minutes.  

I am glad I have this routine in my daily life and thank you Adriene for these 30 day challenges to keep me motivated cause some times it is so easy to say, I won't do it today, I will do it tomorrow ... and for me, I do need that bit of push to say "come on, it is only for 30 minutes, and you know you feel good afterwards" ...

Dear Adriene, it is only day nine, and yet I can already feel many different changes in my body. I am a student, which means that I spend most of my time sitting and crouching over at a desk, often in uncomfortable positions. I have always been aware that to sit that much, and to constantly bear a great deal of stress and pressures with exams and deadlines, makes my muscles tighter, and that I tend to clench on my jaws and my shoulders, but it is only since I have started the True journey with you that I can fully realize where and how I creat all this constant tension. I enjoy jogging very much, and I always thought that in order to release tensions jogging was the best option to come to, but you opened up to me a whole world of new possibilities. I believe as well in the connection of the body to the mind, the soul, and the heart, and I am beyond grateful to have found someone on the Internet (which is rich in extreme and potentially unhealthy fitness practices) who promotes such a balanced practice to stay "fit" not only physically, but also mentally! In order to honestly see how my mind and my body can actually change, I will not do any other kind of sport. I am very curious because in less than two weeks I feel stronger and lighter than I would have ever expected! I have decided to test myself through this journey, and I hope that once it will be (unfortunately) over I will still be able to stick with it (as you often say). Most importantly, this comment is to let you know that I appreciate your work and effort, and that I am very happy that you are doing this for people. You are a very generous person! Thank you very much, Adriene!
